rComments: Great prof, ENV410 was probably my favourite class at U of T. Course material was dense but clearly explained with a narrative arch throughout the course. Prof. Prichard was wonderful at allowing the seminar to be led by students while still guiding it so that we got the most out of it.

Decent professor. Knows his stuff, comes to class with a long and information packed lecture. You will learn a great deal about African politics. However, his TAs mark extremely hard. If you are okay with low grades then take this course. If you care about your GPA then avoid this course.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lecture heavy', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Excellent moderator of class discussion - creates an atmosphere that's comfortable for everyone to speak in bust also directs the conversation to cover the complexities of the material. He's a long-time development practitioner  and has great first-hand experience to illustrate the material. Very approachable and helpful in office hours.

Best course I have taken so far. Very smart, passionate and structured teacher. Does talk fast but he is great speaker which makes it easy to follow him, considering the huge amount of info covered in each lecture. The course is nevertheless very challenging, you need to do the readings.

Very smart and enthusiastic teacher, who obviously knows what he is talking about. Lectures are well structured and he is a great speaker, which makes it easy to follow him, especially considering the HUGE amount of info covered in each lecture. The course is however very challenging cuz readings are a must! (lectures give broader picture)

Wants students to write clearly and succinctly, while his own instructions and feed-backs are long-winded, confusing, and redundant. Lectures failed to capture my attention, although he sounds enthusiastic enough. The papers were graded in a week's times, so I'm guessing the TA spent 15 minutes grading per paper. Keep essays simple.

Dr Prichard is an excellent Professor.  He constantly pushes you to improve your work and think about all aspects of the subject matter.  You have to work it out for yourself sometimes, but this is what you need to do in order to succeed.

One of the worst professors at this institution. He actually turned me away from the subject. Lectures are dry and boring. Extremely unfair marker. Followed guidelines exactly for the midterm, and ended up getting a C- (I'm an A student). Very nit-picky marker, and comments made no sense. I caught him on his marking mistakes numerous times. Avoid.
